{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012GZX1ZH9CMEN5HaErikSeY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The elasticsearch namespace is empty now! The pods are gone. This suggests the namespace was cleaned up. But why?\n\nLooking at the precondition setup flow:\n1. Probe: check if pods are running\n2. If probe fails → apply: delete namespace, recreate, set up everything\n3. Verify: check pods are running\n\nWait, actually with `on_probe_fail: skip`, if the probe FAILS, the whole unit is skipped. But if the probe PASSES (pods are running), it should go to verify... Actually let me re-read.\n \nSo the probe counts running pods with a grep command. If there are running pods, it exits with 0 and the apply step is skipped. If there are no running pods, it also exits with 0 (just returns \"0\"), which means the probe technically succeeds either way—so `on_probe_fail: skip` wouldn't trigger. That means apply should always run, which would delete and recreate the namespace. The precondition must have completed successfully before I started running as the agent, but now the namespace is empty—either another concurrent KARMA test cleaned it up, or the test timed out and performed cleanup. Looking at the run directory structure, the precondition.log exists (indicating it finished), and I'm currently running as the agent, so I need to figure out what state the environment is actually in right now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":669,"cache_read_input_tokens":50245,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":669},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9eb29c50-c508-4f87-8a38-36ea9575a99e","uuid":"ddc907e5-fe1c-4ec5-84d2-5ff26c4832d2","request_id":"req_011CbyB