{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NSrCeV77bA9nWKXbVayE3v","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what was done:\n\n1. **Generated new CA + leaf cert** locally with `openssl` — new 2048-bit RSA CA (CN=es-http-ca-new, 365 days) and a leaf cert (365 days) signed by it, with all required SANs (service DNS names + per-node headless DNS names).\n\n2. **Updated `es-http-tls` Secret** with the new `tls.crt`, `tls.key`, and `ca.crt`.\n\n3. **Updated `es-http-ca` ConfigMap** with the new CA so the `curl-test` pod's mounted volume reflects the new trust anchor.\n\n4. **Rolling restarted `StatefulSet/es-cluster`** — Kubernetes updated pods one at a time (2 → 1 → 0), keeping 2 nodes in service throughout. All 3 pods came up Ready with the new certs.\n\n5. **Oracle verified**: new CA fingerprint ≠ old, leaf validity 365 days (within 300–400 day window), leaf verifies with new CA, fails with old CA, and the HTTPS cluster health check returns `green` via the updated CA."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":390,"cache_read_input_tokens":62697,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":390},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9eb29c50-c508-4f87-8a38-36ea9575a99e","uuid":"52aa7fcb-360d-48f5-a248-72c1adfea37b","request_id":"req_011CbyC6M5cMUESG8LLGMJnb"}
